<br>
Inles  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugroovydancepants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GroovyDancepants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/29/01 1:15:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/briannelson1/eva.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mask of Hunter... please help me figure it out</span><hr size=1> I don't think you shrink at all. If you compare yourself to other people of the same race theres no difference. The slight change in view magnification looks a lot like it does when you shrink. The mana regen and see invis are nice. I haven't seen any evidence of reduced outdoor aggro but I suppose it's possible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unanoqmajicblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanoq MajicBlade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/2/01 4:25:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mask of Hunter... please help me figure it out</span><hr size=1> You will definitely notice the change in distance perception when a mob appears to be farther<br>
away than he or she really is...I cite the Wurms, Chromos and Wyverns in SF for example.  I <br>
usually camp the second  Dragon  Statue past the entrance to The Overthere.  With Mask of<br>
Hunter off, I can cast root on one of the mobs with me being on a ledge to the left of the<br>
Statue (  if you are facing it ) with the mob at the bottom and he will be rooted.  However, <br>
with MoH on, depth perception changes and It appears I need to get closer to the mob to <br>
cast the root which immediately results in me getting hit a couple or three times before pulling <br>
back.  As I said, the Shrink/Magnification is really a change in depth perception...like the <br>
passenger-side side view mirrors on automobiles. But in this case, &quot;Objects (mobs) are closer <br>
than they appear.&quot;<br>
<br>
My 2-cp <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaslethalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maslethalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/9/01 5:51:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mask of Hunter... please help me figure it out</span><hr size=1> I use it for the mana regen, as for the shrink and magnification I only see the screen adjust slightly.  <br>
